1
00:00:10,567 --> 00:00:12,733
<i>We pretend to annoy each other,</i>

2
00:00:12,867 --> 00:00:16,133
<i>but truth is,
we like each other.</i>

3
00:00:16,267 --> 00:00:18,133
<i> Us? That's not happening.</i>

4
00:00:18,267 --> 00:00:19,100
<i> Come on, Selena.</i>

5
00:00:19,233 --> 00:00:20,133
<i>Let's just have
our drinks inside.</i>

6
00:00:20,267 --> 00:00:22,433
<i>My guy is tailing some
kidnappers.</i>

7
00:00:22,567 --> 00:00:25,400
<i>They grabbed victims
from the Calabari Job Fair.</i>

8
00:00:25,533 --> 00:00:26,433
<i> Get the girls ready.</i>

9
00:00:26,567 --> 00:00:28,400
<i>Tomorrow, we will transport
them.</i>

10
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:32,067
<i> That was a gunshot.</i>

11
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:33,700
<i>- What was that?
- Boss, someone got in.</i>

12
00:00:33,867 --> 00:00:35,433
<i> Meet them head-on!</i>

13
00:00:38,267 --> 00:00:39,467
<i>- Lieutenant Paloma.
- Yes, Sir.</i>

14
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:40,700
<i>- You go that way.
- Let's go.</i>

15
00:00:41,833 --> 00:00:43,333
<i>- Have mercy!
- I'm a police! I'm a police!</i>

16
00:00:43,467 --> 00:00:45,100
<i>Thank you,
you didn't leave Tere behind.</i>

17
00:00:45,233 --> 00:00:46,200
<i> You did a good job.</i>

18
00:00:46,333 --> 00:00:47,867
<i>Actually, I've also been
following a syndicate.</i>

19
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:49,433
<i>It's connected to human
trafficking.</i>

20
00:00:49,567 --> 00:00:51,500
<i>And I feel like
they're the ones behind this.</i>

21
00:00:51,633 --> 00:00:54,267
<i> That's Sonny but he's small.</i>

22
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:55,367
<i> No, he's big.</i>

23
00:00:55,500 --> 00:00:56,533
<i> Who's that?</i>

24
00:00:56,667 --> 00:00:58,533
<i> Maybe it's Sonny, haunting us.</i>

25
00:00:58,667 --> 00:01:01,000
<i>You know, I'm not
scared of ghosts.</i>

26
00:01:01,133 --> 00:01:06,567
<i>What scares me are
unexplored feelings.</i>

27
00:01:06,700 --> 00:01:08,500
<i>Why are you watching over
Selena and me?</i>

28
00:01:08,667 --> 00:01:11,833
<i>Just so you know
that I love you.</i>

29
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:39,067
Sir, why are you slapping me?

30
00:01:41,367 --> 00:01:43,800
Sir, don't be like that!

31
00:01:43,933 --> 00:01:45,667
What the heck?
You're overdoing it!

32
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:47,233
Enriquez!

33
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:50,633
Fix yourself, you're dreaming.

34
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:54,367
So you talk while sleeping?

35
00:02:17,667 --> 00:02:19,833
<i> Put your hands up!</i>

36
00:02:25,300 --> 00:02:26,700
Who were you fighting?

37
00:02:26,833 --> 00:02:28,733
No one, it's just...

38
00:02:29,967 --> 00:02:32,233
The thieves.

39
00:02:32,367 --> 00:02:33,600
Thieves?

40
00:02:33,733 --> 00:02:35,767
What did they steal from you?

41
00:02:37,167 --> 00:02:38,667
My charger.

42
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:41,867
What's funny, Sir?

43
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:44,433
Well, you looked like you were
ready to throw punches earlier.

44
00:02:44,567 --> 00:02:46,167
I thought it was something
serious.

45
00:02:46,300 --> 00:02:47,833
Turns out, it's just a charger.

46
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:50,900
And what's it to you?

47
00:02:51,033 --> 00:02:53,633
But that's what I dreamed about.

48
00:02:54,467 --> 00:02:55,567
Fine.

49
00:02:56,367 --> 00:02:58,367
Go to Selena.

50
00:02:58,500 --> 00:02:59,667
Help her get dressed,

51
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:02,433
then get some sleep,
I'll keep watch here.

52
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:05,800
No, wait...

53
00:03:05,933 --> 00:03:08,267
Why don't you just go in there?

54
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:09,600
Go lie beside her,

55
00:03:09,733 --> 00:03:11,667
so you can seal the deal

56
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:14,033
and fully succeed.

57
00:03:14,533 --> 00:03:16,200
She looks like she's about to
give in to you anyway.

58
00:03:16,333 --> 00:03:17,433
Hold on, hold on.

59
00:03:17,567 --> 00:03:21,800
Enriquez, that's not what I
meant by strategy.

60
00:03:22,700 --> 00:03:25,067
I'm not that kind of person.

61
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:25,933
It's fine, Sir.

62
00:03:26,067 --> 00:03:27,900
Just go in.

63
00:03:28,033 --> 00:03:30,800
No, it's fine.
I'll stay outside.

64
00:03:30,933 --> 00:03:34,033
Wait, Bobby.

65
00:03:35,067 --> 00:03:37,133
What's your problem?

66
00:03:37,267 --> 00:03:38,833
I thought we were okay earlier,

67
00:03:38,967 --> 00:03:40,833
now you're acting annoyed again.

68
00:03:40,967 --> 00:03:43,067
I'm not annoyed, Sir.

69
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:45,267
Then what? Are you just
forcing yourself?

70
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:47,700
Did you miss out on something
important?

71
00:03:47,833 --> 00:03:49,867
I'm not forcing anything!

72
00:03:50,733 --> 00:03:52,633
I just have a lot on my mind.

73
00:03:52,767 --> 00:03:54,200
Enriquez, remember,

74
00:03:54,367 --> 00:03:56,100
we're guarding
someone's life here.

75
00:03:56,233 --> 00:03:58,700
Your head needs
to stay in the game.

76
00:03:58,833 --> 00:04:00,600
Wow, really?

77
00:04:00,733 --> 00:04:03,000
Your head's in the game...

78
00:04:03,133 --> 00:04:04,333
yet you're drinking?

79
00:04:04,467 --> 00:04:05,567
I wasn't drinking.

80
00:04:05,700 --> 00:04:08,033
Didn't you hear
what Selena said?

81
00:04:08,167 --> 00:04:09,933
She gets chatty and comfortable

82
00:04:10,067 --> 00:04:11,600
when she drinks.

83
00:04:11,733 --> 00:04:13,167
So I drank with her

84
00:04:13,300 --> 00:04:14,900
so she'd trust me.

85
00:04:15,033 --> 00:04:16,600
Maybe she'd tell me
the real reason

86
00:04:16,733 --> 00:04:18,633
why someone wants her dead.

87
00:04:18,767 --> 00:04:20,500
Even if she didn't
say it outright,

88
00:04:20,633 --> 00:04:22,267
I'm sure she has an idea

89
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:23,667
who Sonny's boss is.

90
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:25,600
And whoever that is...

91
00:04:25,733 --> 00:04:27,167
I'm sure they're behind

92
00:04:27,300 --> 00:04:30,300
the bank robbery
and the kidnappings.

93
00:04:31,367 --> 00:04:32,400
You should've...

94
00:04:32,533 --> 00:04:34,767
You should've told me, Sir.

95
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:38,167
I thought you just wanted
to make a move on Selena.

96
00:04:40,300 --> 00:04:43,800
I'm not that kind of person,
Enriquez.

97
00:04:43,933 --> 00:04:45,733
Sorry, Sir.

98
00:04:46,367 --> 00:04:48,533
So, did she say anything?

99
00:04:48,667 --> 00:04:50,500
Not complete.

100
00:04:51,867 --> 00:04:54,833
But it sounds like
she's pointing to a politician.

101
00:04:55,367 --> 00:04:57,300
So if you could, Enriquez...

102
00:04:57,433 --> 00:04:58,933
go check on Selena,

103
00:04:59,067 --> 00:05:00,300
help her get dressed,

104
00:05:00,433 --> 00:05:01,467
then get some rest.

105
00:05:01,633 --> 00:05:03,367
I just need to check something
in the back.

106
00:05:04,567 --> 00:05:05,600
I'm not sleeping, Sir.

107
00:05:05,733 --> 00:05:07,567
Your call.

108
00:05:28,733 --> 00:05:30,933
This is a safehouse?

109
00:05:31,767 --> 00:05:33,767
Looks like...

110
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:36,500
it's infested with rats.

111
00:05:37,033 --> 00:05:39,533
This must be one
of the old safehouses.

112
00:05:40,067 --> 00:05:41,400
It's okay.

113
00:05:41,533 --> 00:05:43,500
I still have two more here.

114
00:05:43,633 --> 00:05:44,733
Let's go.

115
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:46,900
I'm tired.

116
00:05:48,033 --> 00:05:49,400
Let's do that tomorrow.

117
00:05:49,533 --> 00:05:50,933
What?

118
00:05:51,333 --> 00:05:53,033
I thought you wanted to finish
this job right away?

119
00:05:53,167 --> 00:05:55,167
I said I'm tired.

120
00:05:56,167 --> 00:05:59,200
I don't work when I'm tired.

121
00:06:00,033 --> 00:06:02,433
You're so arrogant.

122
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:52,333
I thought you're not going to
sleep?

123
00:07:00,867 --> 00:07:05,900
Thank you all
for saving my niece...

124
00:07:06,367 --> 00:07:08,600
and the other women,
so quickly.

125
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:10,667
It's nothing, Sir.

126
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:12,933
According to Lieutenant Paloma,

127
00:07:13,067 --> 00:07:17,067
she's pursuing a human
trafficking case.

128
00:07:17,233 --> 00:07:20,067
If you get any info,

129
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:21,800
report it directly to me.

130
00:07:21,933 --> 00:07:23,667
Sir, yes, Sir!

131
00:07:24,267 --> 00:07:26,533
Robles, Dizon,

132
00:07:26,667 --> 00:07:28,667
contact Garcia.

133
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:30,633
Tell him...

134
00:07:30,767 --> 00:07:34,900
we're going to Boss
and Mayor Guerrero's debate.

135
00:07:37,033 --> 00:07:38,700
Yes, Sir!

136
00:07:47,933 --> 00:07:49,933
Hurry up, clean this place!

137
00:07:50,067 --> 00:07:51,600
People are about to arrive.

138
00:07:51,733 --> 00:07:53,767
- Wipe down everything.
- Can you...

139
00:07:53,900 --> 00:07:56,533
- Wipe down everything.
- Yes, Captain, yes, yes.

140
00:07:56,667 --> 00:07:59,000
- Captain.
- What?

141
00:07:59,133 --> 00:08:02,000
So, is the Mayor's family
attending the debate?

142
00:08:02,133 --> 00:08:03,100
Maybe not.

143
00:08:03,233 --> 00:08:04,867
Why, who are you looking for?
The Mayor's kid?

144
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:07,133
- Glen?
- No! I mean, yes.

145
00:08:07,267 --> 00:08:10,067
He's the one I'm hoping to see.

146
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:13,633
I'm team Mysterious Oppa.

147
00:08:13,767 --> 00:08:15,900
Vince, hey!

148
00:08:16,633 --> 00:08:17,867
Have you seen that viral video?

149
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,200
The one with the shooting
those riders?

150
00:08:19,333 --> 00:08:20,167
- Here.
- Let me see.

151
00:08:20,300 --> 00:08:21,233
We were supposed to be there.

152
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:22,233
We weren't able to make it.

153
00:08:22,367 --> 00:08:24,367
Mayor just asked us
to roast the pig.

154
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:26,267
Good thing we didn't go.

155
00:08:26,400 --> 00:08:28,100
Otherwise, we'd just be
another headline.

156
00:08:28,233 --> 00:08:29,167
Good thing.

157
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:31,267
That roast pig saved your lives,
Bro.

158
00:08:31,733 --> 00:08:32,567
I'd choose that any day.

159
00:08:32,700 --> 00:08:34,033
At least, there you're full.

160
00:08:34,167 --> 00:08:36,800
Wait, pause it at the shooter.

161
00:08:36,933 --> 00:08:38,733
Wait...

162
00:08:41,167 --> 00:08:43,033
<i>- Oh, wow. Oh, hey.
- He's handsome.</i>

163
00:08:43,167 --> 00:08:44,633
Sir, you need help?

164
00:08:44,767 --> 00:08:46,367
<i>- Run for your life!
- Yes, there's an exit.</i>

165
00:08:47,767 --> 00:08:48,933
Oh my, Mar...

166
00:08:49,067 --> 00:08:50,833
He looks just like...

167
00:08:50,967 --> 00:08:53,100
He looks like our Mysterious
Oppa!

168
00:08:53,233 --> 00:08:55,633
Could it be him?

169
00:08:55,800 --> 00:08:57,067
He does look like him...

170
00:09:16,033 --> 00:09:18,600
Good morning, Sir Tonyo.

171
00:09:18,733 --> 00:09:19,633
Coffee?

172
00:09:19,767 --> 00:09:21,667
Oh, sure, thank you.

173
00:09:21,967 --> 00:09:24,400
And thank you...

174
00:09:24,533 --> 00:09:26,367
for taking care of me
last night.

175
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:28,333
You also changed my clothes.

176
00:09:28,500 --> 00:09:30,067
Oh...

177
00:09:30,700 --> 00:09:31,933
I didn't changed your clothes.

178
00:09:32,067 --> 00:09:33,633
Who?

179
00:09:35,967 --> 00:09:37,367
- Me.
- Oh.

180
00:09:38,700 --> 00:09:40,933
You were the one who changed
my clothes, Ma'am Bobby?

181
00:09:41,067 --> 00:09:43,333
Thank you?

182
00:09:44,067 --> 00:09:45,600
That means...

183
00:09:45,733 --> 00:09:47,867
nothing happened between us?

184
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:50,100
He's a gentleman.

185
00:09:50,233 --> 00:09:51,833
Oh, shocks.

186
00:09:51,967 --> 00:09:53,067
By the way, Enriquez.

187
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:55,367
Major just called.

188
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:57,633
The assigned officers are on
their way here

189
00:09:57,767 --> 00:09:59,400
to accompany you, Selena.

190
00:09:59,533 --> 00:10:00,400
That came directly

191
00:10:00,533 --> 00:10:02,500
from the Witness Protection
Department.

192
00:10:02,667 --> 00:10:04,033
Lieutenant Jeremy Banaag

193
00:10:04,167 --> 00:10:05,933
and Sergeant Carla Ramos.

194
00:10:06,533 --> 00:10:08,033
That means when they get here,

195
00:10:08,167 --> 00:10:09,467
you're leaving?

196
00:10:09,867 --> 00:10:10,633
Yes.

197
00:10:10,767 --> 00:10:13,233
We're just temporary escorts.

198
00:10:14,933 --> 00:10:16,433
Good morning!

199
00:10:16,567 --> 00:10:17,733
How was your sleep?

200
00:10:17,867 --> 00:10:19,133
Oh, Mister Erning.

201
00:10:19,267 --> 00:10:20,833
- Good morning.
- Good morning!

202
00:10:20,967 --> 00:10:23,967
I bought bread
and some spread for you.

203
00:10:24,100 --> 00:10:25,767
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

204
00:10:25,900 --> 00:10:27,367
There.

205
00:10:28,467 --> 00:10:31,867
Mister Erning, is there a
grocery store nearby?

206
00:10:33,567 --> 00:10:35,367
Mister Erning.

207
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:37,867
Mister Erning!

208
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:39,167
Selena is asking

209
00:10:39,300 --> 00:10:41,367
if there is a grocery near by.

210
00:10:41,500 --> 00:10:44,300
Oh, I can't hear you.

211
00:10:44,433 --> 00:10:46,967
My hearing aid is broken again.

212
00:10:48,633 --> 00:10:49,900
You know...

213
00:10:50,033 --> 00:10:53,033
five were killed in the road
rage yesterday.

214
00:10:53,167 --> 00:10:54,467
Over there in Milagros,

215
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:56,867
and they still manage to escape.

216
00:10:59,167 --> 00:11:01,633
We will check out
three safehouses later.

217
00:11:03,300 --> 00:11:05,633
Okay, then you go by yourself.

218
00:11:05,767 --> 00:11:09,367
Just let me know which house
our targets are really in.

219
00:11:09,533 --> 00:11:11,933
That's the time I will come in.

220
00:11:13,067 --> 00:11:14,867
I'll save my energy.

221
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:16,400
No.

222
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:18,433
You coming with me.

223
00:11:18,567 --> 00:11:20,400
You're not my boss.

224
00:11:31,533 --> 00:11:34,000
Who are we replacing again?

225
00:11:34,967 --> 00:11:37,100
It's Sergeant Barbara Enriquez

226
00:11:37,233 --> 00:11:39,300
and Lieutenant Antonio Conde,

227
00:11:39,433 --> 00:11:40,700
From Station 12.

228
00:11:40,833 --> 00:11:43,667
Do you know the way
to the safe house?

229
00:11:43,833 --> 00:11:45,067
Yes.

230
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:47,100
I think were near.

231
00:11:47,233 --> 00:11:49,833
Wait, let's order first.

232
00:11:50,500 --> 00:11:53,000
Miss, Miss, can we order?

233
00:11:53,133 --> 00:11:55,767
Look at that,
talk about being lucky.

234
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:58,067
Hey.

235
00:11:58,200 --> 00:12:00,067
Those two in the other table,

236
00:12:00,567 --> 00:12:02,167
they're the cops
who will replace

237
00:12:02,300 --> 00:12:04,500
the escorts of our target

238
00:12:06,133 --> 00:12:08,567
Let's wait for them to finish
and then...

239
00:12:09,367 --> 00:12:10,967
we move.

240
00:12:21,967 --> 00:12:23,033
Here, look at this.

241
00:12:23,167 --> 00:12:24,333
They were able to take a video.

242
00:12:24,467 --> 00:12:25,933
There, it has gone viral.

243
00:12:26,067 --> 00:12:28,233
There, there.

244
00:12:32,500 --> 00:12:34,067
<i> They have a gun!</i>

245
00:12:35,500 --> 00:12:37,967
Unbelievable, those people
are monsters.

246
00:12:38,100 --> 00:12:41,167
They kill without fear,
like they have no souls.

247
00:12:41,300 --> 00:12:42,800
Wait...

248
00:12:44,067 --> 00:12:46,233
I think I recognize this gunman.

249
00:12:46,367 --> 00:12:49,133
I just can't remember
where I've seen him.

250
00:12:50,100 --> 00:12:51,533
Sir...

251
00:12:51,667 --> 00:12:54,567
We should've responded
yesterday.

252
00:12:54,700 --> 00:12:56,133
I feel sorry for the victims.

253
00:12:56,267 --> 00:12:57,333
Oh my, no.

254
00:12:57,467 --> 00:12:59,067
It's just right
that we did not interfere there,

255
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:01,200
we could have been shot too.

256
00:13:08,367 --> 00:13:10,100
We're here.

257
00:13:10,233 --> 00:13:11,800
Let's go.

258
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:27,767
You go ahead.
I'll check the trunk.

259
00:13:28,233 --> 00:13:30,100
Be quick.

260
00:13:49,733 --> 00:13:51,400
I think they are here.

261
00:13:51,900 --> 00:13:53,800
Mister Erning...

262
00:13:53,933 --> 00:13:54,867
Mister Erning, I think

263
00:13:55,033 --> 00:13:56,900
the officers raplacing us
are already here...

264
00:13:57,033 --> 00:13:59,200
Can you take a look?

265
00:13:59,833 --> 00:14:01,533
Okay, Chief.

266
00:14:02,033 --> 00:14:03,467
Okay.

267
00:14:10,800 --> 00:14:12,367
Good luck on your debate, Boss.

268
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:16,667
Joaquin's the one
who needs luck more

269
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:18,533
in this face-off.

270
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:21,200
Leslie...

271
00:14:25,067 --> 00:14:28,133
So this is why you stopped
letting me court you.

272
00:14:28,300 --> 00:14:30,333
I heard you said yes to Victor.

273
00:14:30,467 --> 00:14:32,000
I'm sorry, Mayor,

274
00:14:32,133 --> 00:14:37,467
but our vision for Calabari
aligns more with Amo.

275
00:14:38,233 --> 00:14:40,233
You're really insane.

276
00:14:40,367 --> 00:14:42,867
You've stolen everything from
me.

277
00:14:44,933 --> 00:14:47,833
Boss, Mayor, please get ready.

278
00:14:47,967 --> 00:14:49,700
We're starting in a bit.

279
00:14:50,167 --> 00:14:52,067
- All right.
- Excuse me for a moment.

280
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:54,567
We'll talk later, Vice.

281
00:14:57,367 --> 00:14:59,000
So?

282
00:14:59,133 --> 00:15:01,333
You ready to get humiliated?

283
00:15:02,367 --> 00:15:05,033
I came loaded with ammo,
Joaquin.

284
00:15:05,167 --> 00:15:06,933
You might be the one
to fall first.

285
00:15:12,167 --> 00:15:13,933
Please come in, Sir.

286
00:15:18,700 --> 00:15:21,467
I'll just continue
what I'm cooking.

287
00:15:24,667 --> 00:15:27,433
Good day, Lieutenant Banaag.

288
00:15:27,567 --> 00:15:29,233
I'm Lieutenant Antonio Conde

289
00:15:29,367 --> 00:15:31,900
and this is Sergeant Enriquez.

290
00:15:32,433 --> 00:15:34,100
Hi, Sir.

291
00:15:34,233 --> 00:15:36,300
And where's Sergeant Ramos?

292
00:15:36,467 --> 00:15:37,600
Oh...

293
00:15:37,733 --> 00:15:39,900
he's just fixing something
with the car.

294
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:45,033
Lieutenant,
may we check your ID?

295
00:15:45,167 --> 00:15:46,700
Of course.

296
00:15:52,133 --> 00:15:55,000
Miss Selena, good morning.

297
00:15:55,133 --> 00:15:57,267
Oh, good morning to you too.

298
00:15:57,400 --> 00:15:58,267
By the way,

299
00:15:58,400 --> 00:16:00,633
this is Mister Erning,
the caretaker here.

300
00:16:00,767 --> 00:16:02,800
His hearing's a bit off.

301
00:16:02,933 --> 00:16:05,033
His hearing aid
might be broken again.

302
00:16:05,167 --> 00:16:06,767
If you need anything,

303
00:16:06,900 --> 00:16:08,767
just tap him.

304
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:12,933
All right, Selena.

305
00:16:13,067 --> 00:16:14,833
We'll go ahead.

306
00:16:14,967 --> 00:16:17,333
Thank you again.

307
00:16:17,467 --> 00:16:19,667
We'll be seeing
each other again, right?

308
00:16:20,667 --> 00:16:22,500
Yes, we still have an ongoing
investigation,

309
00:16:22,633 --> 00:16:25,100
so we'll definitely meet again.

310
00:16:26,067 --> 00:16:28,600
Enriquez, I'll head
to the car first.

311
00:16:28,733 --> 00:16:29,900
I just need to fix something.

312
00:16:30,033 --> 00:16:30,800
Got it, Sir.

313
00:16:30,933 --> 00:16:32,367
I'll follow after
I grab my things.

314
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:34,633
Lieutenant,
I'll leave it to you.

315
00:16:38,167 --> 00:16:39,933
Sir Jeremy...

316
00:16:40,867 --> 00:16:42,467
Is Major Sevilla

317
00:16:42,633 --> 00:16:45,100
still at the Witness Protection
Department?

318
00:16:45,233 --> 00:16:47,667
Oh, Major Sevilla?

319
00:16:48,367 --> 00:16:50,433
I was just talking to him
before I came here.

320
00:16:50,567 --> 00:16:52,200
He trained me.

321
00:16:52,333 --> 00:16:53,900
He's really kind.

322
00:16:54,033 --> 00:16:56,333
Yes, he is.

323
00:16:58,700 --> 00:16:59,633
Oh...

324
00:16:59,767 --> 00:17:01,733
Please, have a seat.
Come in.

325
00:17:01,867 --> 00:17:03,667
Okay, Sir.

326
00:17:16,933 --> 00:17:19,033
Sir Jeremy...

327
00:17:19,167 --> 00:17:20,067
You look familiar.

328
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:23,900
Haven't we met before?

329
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:30,600
Calabari, good morning!

330
00:17:34,267 --> 00:17:38,633
Are you ready for Debate 2025?

331
00:17:40,367 --> 00:17:44,333
So let's all welcome
the well-known “El Hepe,”

332
00:17:44,467 --> 00:17:46,600
Mayor Joaquin Guerrero!

333
00:17:48,567 --> 00:17:53,300
El Hepe! El Hepe!
El Hepe!

334
00:17:53,433 --> 00:17:56,467
And his challenger for
leadership,

335
00:17:56,600 --> 00:18:02,000
mayoral candidate
Victor “Boss” Santiago!

336
00:18:02,133 --> 00:18:04,467
Boss! Boss! Boss!

337
00:18:04,600 --> 00:18:06,133
Boss! Boss! Boss!

338
00:18:06,267 --> 00:18:07,700
Let's begin.

339
00:18:07,833 --> 00:18:09,200
Our first topic,

340
00:18:09,333 --> 00:18:13,567
the recent string of crimes
in our town.

341
00:18:13,700 --> 00:18:18,800
What is the best way
to reduce this?

342
00:18:18,933 --> 00:18:22,167
First to answer,
Mayor Joaquin Guerrero.

343
00:18:24,167 --> 00:18:27,167
Good morning to you all.

344
00:18:27,700 --> 00:18:31,100
First and foremost,
we need to strengthen

345
00:18:31,233 --> 00:18:33,300
our law enforcement.

346
00:18:33,433 --> 00:18:38,633
We need police visibility
in high-crime areas.

347
00:18:38,767 --> 00:18:42,000
We also need modern tech
for our police...

348
00:18:42,133 --> 00:18:45,033
CCTVs, body cams,

349
00:18:45,167 --> 00:18:48,900
and other gear.

350
00:18:51,667 --> 00:18:54,900
Sir Victor, please
let Mayor finish first.

351
00:18:55,067 --> 00:18:56,033
What's this?

352
00:18:56,167 --> 00:18:58,667
I'm just wondering about your
answers.

353
00:18:58,800 --> 00:19:00,067
How long have you been mayor

354
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:02,333
and you still haven't done
any of that?

355
00:19:02,467 --> 00:19:03,833
Police visibility?

356
00:19:03,967 --> 00:19:05,433
Let me ask
our fellow citizens...

357
00:19:05,567 --> 00:19:09,600
do we see cops patrolling our
streets here in Calabari?

358
00:19:09,733 --> 00:19:11,467
Here, yes, we see plenty,

359
00:19:11,600 --> 00:19:13,633
probably because Mayor
gathered them all...

360
00:19:13,767 --> 00:19:16,500
to guard himself, right?

361
00:19:16,633 --> 00:19:22,567
I don't think I've seen a single
officer wearing a body cam.

362
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:26,167
Boss! Boss! Boss!

363
00:19:26,300 --> 00:19:29,800
Boss! Boss! Boss!

364
00:19:29,967 --> 00:19:33,867
Just last night,
there was a shooting in town.

365
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:36,833
No arrests, not even a suspect.

366
00:19:38,367 --> 00:19:40,233
Mayor's solution?

367
00:19:40,367 --> 00:19:42,200
Throw a lechon feast.

368
00:19:42,333 --> 00:19:45,533
You're adding to the list of top
killers in the Philippines.

369
00:19:45,667 --> 00:19:48,533
You'll just give our people
a heart attack.

370
00:19:48,667 --> 00:19:50,300
What is that?

371
00:19:50,900 --> 00:19:55,433
Boss! Boss! Boss! Boss!

372
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:09,433
Sergeant Ramos!

373
00:20:13,100 --> 00:20:14,767
Do you need help?

374
00:20:21,367 --> 00:20:23,200
Sergeant...

375
00:20:28,533 --> 00:20:30,333
Sergeant...

376
00:20:38,433 --> 00:20:40,333
Miss Selena...

377
00:20:40,467 --> 00:20:42,700
We haven't met before.

378
00:20:42,833 --> 00:20:44,500
Really?

379
00:20:44,633 --> 00:20:45,867
Feels like I've seen you before,

380
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:47,867
I just can't remember where.

381
00:20:48,833 --> 00:20:49,967
Sir!

382
00:20:50,100 --> 00:20:51,800
I'm cooking<i> pakbet</i> .

383
00:20:55,533 --> 00:20:59,467
Is Mister Erning really deaf?

384
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:03,033
Yes, his hearing's gotten
really bad.

385
00:21:04,200 --> 00:21:05,533
Okay.

386
00:21:05,667 --> 00:21:08,200
You really look familiar to me.

387
00:21:08,833 --> 00:21:12,733
Don't you know my ex, Sonny?

388
00:21:13,967 --> 00:21:16,267
So Major Sevilla
is here after all.

389
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:19,400
I thought he had
a serious illness?

390
00:21:34,833 --> 00:21:36,467
<i> Is Major Sevilla</i>

391
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:38,733
<i> still in Witness Protection?</i>

392
00:21:38,867 --> 00:21:41,000
<i> Ah, si Major Sevilla?</i>

393
00:21:41,133 --> 00:21:43,800
<i>Ah, yes. I was just talking
to him before coming here.</i>

394
00:22:10,867 --> 00:22:13,633
Let go of me!

395
00:22:29,367 --> 00:22:31,100
Put your gun down.

396
00:22:34,567 --> 00:22:35,867
What did you say?

397
00:22:37,467 --> 00:22:41,500
Put your gun down.

398
00:22:43,433 --> 00:22:45,033
Okay.

399
00:22:57,733 --> 00:22:59,533
Sir, what are you doing?

400
00:23:41,433 --> 00:23:43,967
Sir, good thing you're the one
on watch now.

401
00:23:47,067 --> 00:23:48,833
I feel more at ease now.

402
00:24:01,167 --> 00:24:04,200
I don't have any problem
with Sir Tonyo.

403
00:24:08,067 --> 00:24:09,667
Just his companion.

404
00:24:22,133 --> 00:24:25,833
You know, Sir, when I saw
Ma'am Bobby last night...

405
00:24:26,833 --> 00:24:29,700
I said, what a beautiful
police officer.

406
00:24:29,867 --> 00:24:32,467
She looked so demure
and soft-spoken.

407
00:24:34,567 --> 00:24:37,467
The type who doesn't even know
how to fight or argue.

408
00:24:38,433 --> 00:24:40,533
What if someone attacks here?

409
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:45,733
Ma'am Bobby might
just get beaten up.

410
00:24:48,767 --> 00:24:50,733
She doesn't even know
how to fight.

411
00:24:55,033 --> 00:24:56,067
As you can see,

412
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:59,733
he's fit and looks like he's
used to combat.

413
00:25:05,300 --> 00:25:06,967
Come on.

414
00:25:38,967 --> 00:25:41,300
By the way, how do you like
your pakbet?

415
00:25:41,433 --> 00:25:44,000
Half-cooked or soft vegetables?

416
00:25:44,133 --> 00:25:48,000
They say vegetables help you
live longer.

417
00:25:48,133 --> 00:25:50,233
Half-cooked po, Mister.

418
00:26:02,367 --> 00:26:04,600
Call an ambulance!

419
00:26:34,200 --> 00:26:35,400
Sir.

420
00:26:35,533 --> 00:26:36,900
Where's Selena?

421
00:26:37,033 --> 00:26:38,633
Selena is secured, Sir.

422
00:26:38,767 --> 00:26:39,567
She just lost consciousness,

423
00:26:39,700 --> 00:26:41,700
but I already called
for an ambulance.

424
00:26:41,833 --> 00:26:42,533
The guy who pretended
to be a cop

425
00:26:42,700 --> 00:26:44,767
has been neutralized.

426
00:26:44,900 --> 00:26:47,000
He's killed a lot already.

427
00:26:48,467 --> 00:26:51,833
He was the gunman at the fiesta.

428
00:26:52,600 --> 00:26:54,567
Also the one who shot the riders

429
00:26:54,700 --> 00:26:56,933
and the police officers
who were supposed to replace us.

430
00:26:57,067 --> 00:26:57,833
What?

431
00:26:57,967 --> 00:27:00,300
They're desperate
to silence Selena.

432
00:27:01,533 --> 00:27:03,733
That's why she needs
to talk now.

433
00:27:04,267 --> 00:27:06,700
She needs to say
everything she knows.

434
00:27:07,167 --> 00:27:10,667
So, Enriquez, we're taking her
to the hospital.

435
00:27:11,600 --> 00:27:12,700
Yes, Sir.

436
00:27:12,833 --> 00:27:14,233
Oh right, Enriquez.

437
00:27:14,367 --> 00:27:16,800
Change Selena's clothes first

438
00:27:16,967 --> 00:27:18,633
before bringing her
to the hospital.

439
00:27:18,767 --> 00:27:19,900
Change, Sir?

440
00:27:20,033 --> 00:27:22,267
Yes, change her clothes.

441
00:27:23,533 --> 00:27:26,167
Conservative, Sir?

442
00:27:26,733 --> 00:27:28,433
Just do it.

443
00:27:29,100 --> 00:27:30,900
Yes, Sir.

444
00:27:34,867 --> 00:27:36,867
Selena confided in me earlier.

445
00:27:37,000 --> 00:27:38,100
The one they're pointing to as
their boss

446
00:27:38,233 --> 00:27:41,133
and the mastermind behind
the case we're investigating...

447
00:27:41,267 --> 00:27:43,500
is none other than
Victor Santiago.

448
00:27:43,633 --> 00:27:44,667
Can I talk to you?

449
00:27:44,800 --> 00:27:45,800
I already sent a hitman

450
00:27:45,933 --> 00:27:47,200
to take care of the two
witnesses.

451
00:27:47,333 --> 00:27:49,800
And besides, we have no idea
where Selena is.

452
00:27:49,967 --> 00:27:51,867
-Stop!
-So how can you finish your work

453
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:53,300
without knowing anything?

454
00:27:53,433 --> 00:27:55,800
- We know nothing.
- Let's see.

455
00:27:55,933 --> 00:27:59,367
- Power of the sun!
- Power of the sun!

456
00:27:59,500 --> 00:28:01,833
- We carry the light.
- We carry the light.

457
00:28:01,967 --> 00:28:04,233
- Twin strength.
- Twin strength.

458
00:28:04,367 --> 00:28:06,633
- We are the Supertwins!
- We are the Supertwins!

459
00:28:08,567 --> 00:28:10,367
Lieutenant Conde,
what are you doing here?

460
00:28:10,500 --> 00:28:12,767
I'm looking for a criminal.
A thief.

461
00:28:12,900 --> 00:28:13,733
What did they steal, Sir?

462
00:28:13,867 --> 00:28:15,200
My heart.
